ast.name: meetup
ast.comment: Allows to create requests against the Yammer Open Graph.

body.text: This library helps building Yammer apps. See https://developer.yammer.com/ for more details.
## Registering a Yammer app
Before you get started, you will need to create a Yammer app (if you have not done so). Start from here:
* https://www.yammer.com/client_applications
Once you've created your Yammer app, expand the `Basic Info` and enter the following url in the `Redirect URI` textbox:
* https://www.touchdevelop.com/{var:userid}/oauth
This redirect uri is unique for each user. Don't forget to check `Token?` next to the `Redirect URI` box.
Go to `Open Graph` and fill in the `Namespace` information.
## Authentication
Grab your Yammer Client ID (NOT the secret!) and pass it to the `authentication` action. Do not worry about leaking this id; it is designed to be public.
## Posting to the Yammer wall
A common Yammer activity is to post a message to your wall. This is done through the `post text`, `post message` or `post link` actions.
* posting a simple message
## Creating requests
You can use the `create request` action to craft more specialized requests against the Yammer API.
The library will append the access token as needed; and will refresh the token if necessary.
Once you have the request object, you can set the additional parameters and send it away!
Authenticates the user with the given application.
Creates a Yammer API request with the given path and additional query arguments. Authenticates the user if needed. Returns invalid if authentication failed.
Posts a message to the current user Yammer wall and returns the ID of the generated message if successful.
Sends the Yammer API request and tries to handle gracefully errors.
